  "text": "given between preconditioning and the onset of sustained ischemia rendered the heart refractory to preconditioning w x 4,6-10 and that PKC activators administered prior to w x ischemia limited infarct size 6,7 . On the other hand, there w x are studies arguing against the PKC hypotheses 11-13 . w x Przyklenk et al. [CITATION_1] reported that PKC inhibitors failed to block infarct size limitation by preconditioning in the dog. w x In a study using pig hearts by Vogt et al. 12 , preconditioning with 2 cycles of ischemiarreperfusion caused translocation of PKC, but PKC inhibitors did not alter the infarct size limitation by preconditioning. Most recently, w x Valhause et al. [CITATION_2] also showed that preconditioning in the pig heart was not inhibited by staurosporine. The reason for these reported discrepant effects of PKC inhibitors remains unclear.",
